1
00:00:56,060 --> 00:01:00,140
[10 days ago]
[Congratulations on your 70th Birthday Party]

2
00:01:34,845 --> 00:01:37,165
Your mother's tastes are still the same.

3
00:01:37,165 --> 00:01:41,653
No, she is more obsessed with
defi than bulk lately.

4
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:44,313
Defi?

5
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:46,337
Definition.

6
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:50,811
Definition of muscle tone?

7
00:01:52,154 --> 00:01:54,614
Never mind, just give her the gift.

8
00:01:57,909 --> 00:02:01,820
- You think she'll like it?
- Nothing is good enough for my Mom.

9
00:02:06,421 --> 00:02:10,813
Still. What do you want me to say?

10
00:02:10,813 --> 00:02:14,733
Just give her the gift already.
It's my money, after all.

11
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:19,931
Anyway, what is it?
Don't you think that's a bit small?

12
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:23,645
Something she can use
when she signs the contract.

13
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,771
A fountain pen.

14
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:29,586
With her initial.

15
00:02:29,586 --> 00:02:32,109
Studded with diamonds.

16
00:02:32,109 --> 00:02:33,879
Made in Germany.

17
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:45,674
- Excuse me.
- Hi.

18
00:02:45,674 --> 00:02:47,250
Happy 70th birthday.

19
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:52,033
- Oh.
- I got this gift for you.

20
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:56,082
- You can use it when you sign.
- Did they come?

21
00:03:24,288 --> 00:03:25,868
You're here.

22
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:29,782
Here, have some food.

23
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,246
What about my money?

24
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:37,545
Do you think she'd be as generous with me
if I took my shirt off?

25
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,217
- But you don't have the body for it.
- So?

26
00:03:43,045 --> 00:03:45,308
Alright, I get it.
Let's step outside and talk.

27
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,435
Mrs. Jeon!

28
00:03:46,435 --> 00:03:49,100
What's wrong with you? Why are you calling her?

29
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:52,316
What do you mean?
I have to ask her for the money you owe.

30
00:03:52,316 --> 00:03:56,778
Her only son-in-law might lose his organ
because of the private loans.

31
00:03:56,778 --> 00:04:01,033
I told you to wait a little while.

32
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:04,161
You should mind your manners.

33
00:04:04,161 --> 00:04:06,878
My manner? Yes, manner.

34
00:04:10,447 --> 00:04:13,153
Wait for a sec. It hurts.

35
00:04:14,810 --> 00:04:16,286
Fine, fine.

36
00:04:16,286 --> 00:04:17,799
You have one week.

37
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:21,470
Tell your mother-in-law, you idiot.

38
00:04:21,470 --> 00:04:24,320
Or I'll do it for you.

39
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:31,725
[Real Capital &amp; Global Partners]
[Regarding Su Jong's Debt]

40
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:35,369
Now you can say
your final goodbye to the deceased.

41
00:06:40,393 --> 00:06:42,303
Now, please excuse us.

42
00:07:06,802 --> 00:07:10,008
Hey, what are you doing?

43
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:15,333
Hey, didn't you say
you'd be at the funeral all night?

44
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:19,440
Oh, I came to get something.

45
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:22,340
Sure, go ahead.

46
00:07:28,993 --> 00:07:31,994
Isn't that your wife?

47
00:07:31,994 --> 00:07:34,682
What happened? Why is she here?

48
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:39,429
I kidnapped her.

49
00:07:39,429 --> 00:07:41,246
Excuse me?

50
00:07:41,246 --> 00:07:43,266
What does that mean?

51
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:46,349
Like I said, I kidnapped her.

52
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:03,115
How much did you lose?

53
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:06,580
Is that important?

54
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:08,863
You got money?

55
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:10,866
Are you out of your mind?

56
00:08:10,866 --> 00:08:13,313
What have you done?

57
00:08:13,313 --> 00:08:17,780
It's not too late, so just take her home.
I'll call a cab. Okay?

58
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:21,668
If someone finds out,
just tell them you rescued her.

59
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:23,253
Are you crazy?

60
00:08:23,253 --> 00:08:26,579
Rescue her? Do I look like Tom Cruise?

61
00:08:28,046 --> 00:08:30,640
Listen to me.

62
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:33,086
I'm being serious here.

63
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,973
This is my last chance.

64
00:08:38,506 --> 00:08:40,979
You are not making any sense.

65
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:43,964
We can't let people
walking all over us anymore.

66
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:51,081
I'll let you in.

67
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,754
500 million won.

68
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:03,794
No, it's not right.

69
00:09:03,794 --> 00:09:09,383
I'll contact Gyun's friend and find a way out.

70
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:11,363
Su Jong.

71
00:09:12,006 --> 00:09:14,039
Su Jong!

72
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:16,812
It's not what you think.

73
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:20,340
I'm just getting my money in advance.
I will inherit it anyway.

74
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:23,104
As long as I get paid, no one gets hurt.

75
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:26,373
There's no need to feel guilty.

76
00:09:26,373 --> 00:09:28,360
- Hey.
- So annoying.

77
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:30,660
Hey, give it back.

78
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:34,199
- No.
- Give me my phone. Come on, give it back.

79
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:35,367
I said give my phone back.

80
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:38,780
I said no, I said no. I said no!

81
00:09:43,921 --> 00:09:46,670
Hey, let it go!

82
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:49,707
Come on!

83
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:58,473
Hey, are you okay?

84
00:09:58,473 --> 00:09:59,985
What the hell?

85
00:10:03,743 --> 00:10:05,612
Why did you take my phone...

86
00:10:05,612 --> 00:10:08,306
Here, take it.

87
00:10:08,306 --> 00:10:10,277
Suit yourself.

88
00:10:10,277 --> 00:10:13,572
Have fun living with all that debt.

89
00:10:13,572 --> 00:10:16,449
That's not very nice.

90
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:18,942
Look what you did, you asshole.

91
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,220
I'm bleeding!

92
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:24,541
Let's stop the bleeding and get it disinfected.

93
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,919
This is so annoying.

94
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:30,199
I'll take care of everything else, okay?

95
00:10:30,199 --> 00:10:34,620
You just need to look after
my wife in the freezer. Just two days.

96
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:37,208
Two days...

97
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:40,780
You need to...

98
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:42,266
inject...

99
00:10:43,939 --> 00:10:47,676
this syringe three times a day.

100
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,920
But is she going to be okay?

101
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,240
Hey.

102
00:10:55,247 --> 00:10:57,580
It's safe.

103
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:59,800
She's my wife, after all.

104
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,547
<i>Have you decided?</i>

105
00:11:17,493 --> 00:11:19,820
<i>It's really safe, right?</i>

106
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:10,271
I can't believe I'm actually doing this.

107
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,588
You're freezing.

108
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:24,630
I am sorry.

109
00:13:43,949 --> 00:13:47,434
[Dad, where are you?]

110
00:13:59,548 --> 00:14:01,392
[I'm in the building, but you are not around.]

111
00:14:29,661 --> 00:14:31,301
Hey.

112
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,165
What's going on?

113
00:14:34,165 --> 00:14:36,429
It's too dusty in there.

114
00:14:37,503 --> 00:14:40,564
[Mom's not doing well.]

115
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:44,008
Yes, right.

116
00:14:45,397 --> 00:14:47,657
Let's go home.

117
00:15:27,220 --> 00:15:29,179
[Mom, please eat some.]

118
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:34,016
[Dad brought your favorite porridge]

119
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:35,352
[from Buam-dong.]

120
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:13,098
Da Rae.

121
00:16:13,098 --> 00:16:14,838
I can see that.

122
00:16:19,566 --> 00:16:21,766
Do you have anything to say?

123
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,867
I am sorry.

124
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:32,887
That's it?

125
00:16:33,774 --> 00:16:36,273
I'll try to do better.

126
00:16:36,273 --> 00:16:38,764
I am not talking about that.

127
00:16:39,808 --> 00:16:43,091
Something is off with you lately.

128
00:16:43,091 --> 00:16:46,033
You and Gyun were like brothers.

129
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:49,332
But you didn't shed
a single tear at the funeral.

130
00:16:49,332 --> 00:16:53,512
And you were preoccupied with something else.

131
00:16:53,512 --> 00:16:57,226
Even after the cremation, you just disappeared.

132
00:16:57,226 --> 00:16:59,358
How could you do that?

133
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:02,689
Aren't you sad at all?

134
00:17:02,689 --> 00:17:04,397
Gyun is...

135
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:10,140
Gyun is dead.

136
00:17:15,311 --> 00:17:18,621
I know you're worried about the building.

137
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:22,540
But what is the most important thing?
It's family.

138
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:24,240
You should be there for us.

139
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:26,989
Be there when we need you.

140
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,892
You look terrible.

141
00:18:19,892 --> 00:18:22,352
Let's get you changed.

142
00:18:24,033 --> 00:18:25,589
Thank you.

143
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,360
Thank you.

144
00:18:37,793 --> 00:18:41,639
You must be a trendsetter
if you're looking around here.

145
00:18:41,639 --> 00:18:43,205
You know this cafe?

146
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:45,334
- It's the hottest spot in the area.
- Hello, there.

147
00:18:45,334 --> 00:18:47,307
Hello, sir!

148
00:18:47,307 --> 00:18:50,798
Let's look at the vacant room
on the second floor and then the basement.

149
00:18:50,798 --> 00:18:54,824
- Do you want to use a refrigerated warehouse?
- Yes, I want to see.

150
00:18:59,313 --> 00:19:03,102
Let's order some boiled pork
and tofu kimchi for you.

151
00:19:10,313 --> 00:19:12,818
This place hasn't changed.

152
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:15,405
Gyun loved this place.

153
00:19:15,405 --> 00:19:16,865
I know.

154
00:19:16,865 --> 00:19:20,666
He really loved boiled pork here.

155
00:19:20,666 --> 00:19:24,260
The building owner isn't answering the phone.

156
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:26,480
Let's check the second floor.

157
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:35,716
What happened to the money for
Da Rae's school in abroad?

158
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:39,390
I had to use it for something else,
but I'll get it back soon.

159
00:19:41,097 --> 00:19:43,520
[You went too far this time, Dad.]

160
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:47,232
I'm sorry, darling. I will make it up to you.

161
00:19:47,232 --> 00:19:48,852
Trust me.

162
00:19:50,479 --> 00:19:55,180
From now on, tell me everything.
I want to help.

163
00:19:55,180 --> 00:19:57,380
Of course.

164
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,926
[Hee Ju, Real Estate,
Someone wants to see the basement.]

165
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,873
Who is it?

166
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:09,870
It's the realtor lady.

167
00:20:09,870 --> 00:20:13,080
- That woman with leggings?
- Yes.

168
00:20:13,860 --> 00:20:16,048
I don't like her.

169
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:19,135
Why? She could be helpful.

170
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:28,853
Honey.

171
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:33,500
I need to use the bathroom.

172
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:49,374
- Here we are.
- Yes.

173
00:20:49,374 --> 00:20:51,327
Take a look at the rooftop too.

174
00:20:51,327 --> 00:20:53,160
It's great, isn't it?

175
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:57,280
I liked the vacant room,
and this space is great too.

176
00:20:57,280 --> 00:21:02,480
If you're interested, I can put in a good word
with the owner to help you get settled.

177
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,800
<i>Please leave a message...</i>

178
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,960
God damn it.

179
00:21:29,266 --> 00:21:34,247
This area will grow even more
once it's redeveloped.

180
00:21:34,247 --> 00:21:36,600
It's scheduled for redevelopment?

181
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:40,120
- Not this building.
- Good to hear.

182
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,219
Is the refrigerated storage in the basement?

183
00:21:42,219 --> 00:21:45,019
Sure, just give me a second.

184
00:21:46,348 --> 00:21:47,877
[Missed Call]

185
00:21:50,862 --> 00:21:52,674
[Su Jong, Se Yoon Building owner]

186
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:57,960
<i>The phone number
you have dialed is not available...</i>

187
00:21:58,776 --> 00:22:02,238
Would you like to see the basement
while you are here?

188
00:22:02,238 --> 00:22:03,906
Sure.

189
00:22:05,492 --> 00:22:07,212
Taxi!

190
00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:09,999
What the hell is wrong with him?

191
00:22:09,999 --> 00:22:15,999
Excuse me, my phone battery died.
Can I make a quick phone call?

192
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:19,173
Please? Just one call.

193
00:22:19,173 --> 00:22:22,113
I'll give you 1000 won, please?

194
00:22:25,673 --> 00:22:27,218
Taxi!

195
00:22:29,853 --> 00:22:33,660
- What are you doing? I called this cab.
- What?

196
00:22:57,836 --> 00:23:01,236
What the...

197
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:04,120
Unbelievable.

198
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:17,860
- Hi.
- Hi!

199
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:19,983
- Are you going down to see the basement?
- Yes.

200
00:23:19,983 --> 00:23:21,777
Is that storage even working?

201
00:23:21,777 --> 00:23:23,662
Why? It seemed fine.

202
00:23:23,662 --> 00:23:26,722
I stored coffee beans there

203
00:23:26,722 --> 00:23:29,783
but he asked me to take them out
to fix the storage.

204
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:31,846
Would you like to go check it now?

205
00:23:31,846 --> 00:23:34,288
- You got the key?
- Of course.

206
00:23:34,288 --> 00:23:35,419
Sure, I will go then.

207
00:23:35,419 --> 00:23:39,695
Anyway, I've been calling him.

208
00:23:59,605 --> 00:24:03,280
He was looking far ahead...

209
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:06,654
and set up this refrigerated storage.

210
00:24:06,654 --> 00:24:11,019
He thought it would be helpful
to tenants one day.

211
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,952
You're pretty lucky, aren't you?

212
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:17,790
Doesn't it feel a little spooky, though?

213
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:19,500
Right?

214
00:24:20,232 --> 00:24:22,733
Okay, let's see.

215
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:24,957
Is it this one?

216
00:24:31,072 --> 00:24:33,605
I think I hear something.

217
00:24:36,426 --> 00:24:38,435
What are you talking about?

218
00:24:38,435 --> 00:24:40,813
You're being ridiculous.

219
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:47,117
I can really hear something. Right?

220
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,760
Maybe.

221
00:25:06,699 --> 00:25:08,425
I hear nothing.

222
00:25:09,801 --> 00:25:11,368
Come on.

223
00:25:13,252 --> 00:25:15,472
Oh, it's this one.

224
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:25,817
Wait, wait, stop!

225
00:25:25,817 --> 00:25:27,937
Oh my god!

226
00:25:29,109 --> 00:25:31,613
You can't go in there.

227
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:33,728
You startled me!

228
00:25:33,728 --> 00:25:38,121
You can't go in there without my permission.
You could get electrocuted.

229
00:25:38,121 --> 00:25:39,747
Sorry, but you didn't answer the phone.

230
00:25:39,747 --> 00:25:42,334
A water leak caused the short circuit.
Step aside.

231
00:25:42,334 --> 00:25:44,256
Really?

232
00:25:47,420 --> 00:25:51,202
- Seriously, you could have gotten hurt.
- Oh, that was the sound.

233
00:25:51,202 --> 00:25:52,980
I have to get it fixed.

234
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:55,859
[Phyeongbuk Restaurant]

235
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:06,371
[Is he constipated or something?]

236
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:12,738
I'll check the bathroom.

237
00:26:25,806 --> 00:26:27,836
- Is it you?
- Pardon?

238
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:29,672
Who is asking?

239
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:42,760
<i>The phone number you have dialed
is not available...</i>

240
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:46,560
<i>Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

241
00:26:47,149 --> 00:26:51,086
You could've told me that earlier.

242
00:26:51,086 --> 00:26:54,126
Sorry for not letting you know sooner.

243
00:26:54,126 --> 00:26:57,533
So what's the deal with that storage?

244
00:26:57,533 --> 00:27:00,260
The pipe burst, and it's completely flooded.

245
00:27:00,260 --> 00:27:03,373
That's why I mentioned the electric shock.

246
00:27:03,373 --> 00:27:06,992
That kind of thing actually never happens.

247
00:27:06,992 --> 00:27:08,168
That's right.

248
00:27:08,168 --> 00:27:13,280
But I can get it fixed easily
so don't worry about it.

249
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:16,178
Then let's check out the basement
some other time.

250
00:27:16,178 --> 00:27:18,180
How's the refrigerated system working?

251
00:27:18,180 --> 00:27:21,642
It works great with no issues.

252
00:27:21,642 --> 00:27:26,855
If you sign the contract,
I'll handle the rest perfectly.

253
00:27:26,855 --> 00:27:32,319
- He's a really good person, you can trust him.
- That's right.

254
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:36,860
He got this cafe tenant
with really good deals too.

255
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:40,410
Sure, please excuse me for a second.

256
00:27:40,410 --> 00:27:43,921
This is the right place for you. He's...

257
00:27:45,374 --> 00:27:48,733
- What's going on?
- Are you done?

258
00:27:48,733 --> 00:27:50,379
How's my wife?

259
00:27:50,379 --> 00:27:53,454
She's fine. I got her a blanket.

260
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,677
Oh, I forgot.

261
00:27:56,677 --> 00:27:58,940
The syringe.

262
00:27:58,940 --> 00:28:00,560
Hey.

263
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:05,740
Where is the syringe?

264
00:28:05,740 --> 00:28:08,770
Take it out. Come on.

265
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:11,108
Where is it?

266
00:28:11,108 --> 00:28:13,226
Huh?

267
00:28:18,673 --> 00:28:23,033
[Refrigerated storage
Authorized Personnel Only]

268
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:53,165
God damn it.

269
00:28:54,060 --> 00:28:56,500
This is ridiculous.

270
00:29:04,034 --> 00:29:06,325
She's really strong.

271
00:29:06,325 --> 00:29:09,610
You should've taken care of that.

272
00:29:09,610 --> 00:29:11,300
Are you Okay?

273
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:14,680
When are you taking her back?

274
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:16,757
- When the time comes.
- Hey!

275
00:29:16,757 --> 00:29:21,657
By the way,
there's something else you need to do.

276
00:29:23,319 --> 00:29:25,179
What is it?

277
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:32,230
[If you want to save your wife,
get three billion won ready. I'll only talk to you.]

278
00:29:41,905 --> 00:29:45,333
- I need to talk to them.
- Excuse me?

279
00:29:45,333 --> 00:29:47,613
Why do you look so surprised?

280
00:29:49,706 --> 00:29:54,546
They said they would only communicate with me.

281
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:59,613
You expect me to just
hand over three billion won?

282
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:05,472
That's not how deals work.

283
00:30:05,472 --> 00:30:07,307
A deal?

284
00:30:08,015 --> 00:30:12,674
- Your daughter is kidnapped...
- Then...

285
00:30:12,674 --> 00:30:14,815
it's the...

286
00:30:14,815 --> 00:30:17,055
biggest deal ever.

287
00:30:18,473 --> 00:30:22,653
Do you know what is most important in a deal?

288
00:30:25,353 --> 00:30:27,572
Seed money?

289
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:34,793
It's about your attitude.

290
00:30:34,793 --> 00:30:40,257
If you let people think you're a doormat,
then that's what you become.

291
00:30:40,257 --> 00:30:44,961
Can't you get that through your thick skull?

292
00:30:46,597 --> 00:30:48,546
That sounds dangerous.

293
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:50,577
I'm done talking.

294
00:30:52,019 --> 00:30:53,452
It's easy.

295
00:30:53,452 --> 00:30:56,190
All you need to do is make the call and act.

296
00:30:56,190 --> 00:30:59,570
- What acting?
- Pretend to be the kidnapper.

297
00:31:00,159 --> 00:31:02,779
Call her tomorrow morning...

298
00:31:02,779 --> 00:31:04,805
And tell her to meet me at 10pm

299
00:31:04,805 --> 00:31:09,546
at the parking lot of Bukwang Sky Road.

300
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:13,764
This is not what we discussed.
You said you'll be here with money.

301
00:31:13,764 --> 00:31:17,794
Things have changed, buddy. Is that so hard?

302
00:31:17,794 --> 00:31:19,787
Just pretend you're in a movie.

303
00:31:19,787 --> 00:31:22,608
What if she catches me?

304
00:31:23,926 --> 00:31:27,262
She's a 70-year-old woman.

305
00:31:27,262 --> 00:31:32,666
And this is a burner phone
so don't make any other calls on it.

306
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,956
[You are unbelievable...]

307
00:31:53,956 --> 00:31:56,834
We've finished
all the administrative steps here.

308
00:31:56,834 --> 00:31:59,256
What about the others
who are still holding out?

309
00:32:01,002 --> 00:32:02,756
It's nearly done.

310
00:32:02,756 --> 00:32:05,327
I sent the certificate of content proof

311
00:32:05,327 --> 00:32:08,262
and it will be auctioned off soon.

312
00:32:08,262 --> 00:32:10,007
What about the court?

313
00:32:10,007 --> 00:32:15,540
We'll hire the appraiser
who got the order to match the amount.

314
00:32:15,540 --> 00:32:18,840
Alright, next.

315
00:32:19,527 --> 00:32:23,926
The Hanmaeum Building will take a bit longer.

316
00:32:25,404 --> 00:32:28,115
She's from around here

317
00:32:28,115 --> 00:32:31,775
and she won't listen to anything.

318
00:32:37,466 --> 00:32:40,119
That old lady.

319
00:32:40,119 --> 00:32:44,553
She's related to that old man, right?

320
00:32:48,699 --> 00:32:50,345
So, when will you get it done?

321
00:32:50,345 --> 00:32:53,307
I told you to secure
all the buildings scheduled

322
00:32:53,307 --> 00:32:58,234
for redevelopment,
but you're not getting it done.

323
00:32:59,730 --> 00:33:02,399
There was an accident recently

324
00:33:02,399 --> 00:33:06,396
- and you told me to lie low.
- An accident?

325
00:33:08,155 --> 00:33:10,282
You killed a cop.

326
00:33:10,282 --> 00:33:12,534
Do you know how hard

327
00:33:12,534 --> 00:33:16,496
it was to clean up your mess?

328
00:33:16,496 --> 00:33:20,219
- There's a reason...
- A reason?

329
00:33:20,219 --> 00:33:23,504
Are you trying to blame this on me?

330
00:33:23,504 --> 00:33:25,339
Well...

331
00:33:25,339 --> 00:33:28,153
Well?

332
00:33:28,153 --> 00:33:31,261
I told you to finish the job, no matter what.

333
00:33:31,261 --> 00:33:36,571
But no one can find out about Real Capital.

334
00:33:37,935 --> 00:33:40,315
Don't you remember?

335
00:33:42,300 --> 00:33:45,520
I do. I am sorry, sir.

336
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:48,695
Did you hear the news from headquarters?

337
00:33:48,695 --> 00:33:50,781
What news?

338
00:33:50,781 --> 00:33:53,147
Singapore.

339
00:33:53,147 --> 00:33:55,160
They are getting all the focus now.

340
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:57,037
Singapore?

341
00:33:57,037 --> 00:33:59,164
Don't you know what that means?

342
00:33:59,164 --> 00:34:01,766
We're all screwed.

343
00:34:01,766 --> 00:34:06,964
If this redevelopment gets delayed any longer

344
00:34:06,964 --> 00:34:08,880
we are both finished.

345
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,634
Get it done.

346
00:34:10,634 --> 00:34:13,094
Fast.

347
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:15,347
Fast and clean.

348
00:34:15,347 --> 00:34:19,367
And do it legally this time.

349
00:34:21,093 --> 00:34:23,033
Yes, sir.

350
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:31,460
What did he say?

351
00:34:35,226 --> 00:34:38,066
Should I go ahead with the plan?

352
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:42,100
Hold on a second. He wants me to go easy.

353
00:34:42,100 --> 00:34:46,440
This isn't the first time
we've killed someone here.

354
00:34:47,588 --> 00:34:51,550
So, should I dig up the body
I buried in the basement?

355
00:34:51,550 --> 00:34:57,640
No, that will look like an accident,
so don't worry.

356
00:34:57,640 --> 00:34:59,520
Yes, ma'am.

357
00:35:00,809 --> 00:35:02,227
Is there anything else?

358
00:35:02,227 --> 00:35:07,438
Oh, we were supposed to have dinner together.

359
00:35:27,753 --> 00:35:30,895
I've kidnapped your daughter.

360
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:36,929
I've kidnapped your daughter.

361
00:35:36,929 --> 00:35:39,933
No, that's not it.

362
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:43,980
I kidnapped your... Wait, who is that?

363
00:35:44,853 --> 00:35:47,204
You're Ki Su Jong, aren't you?

364
00:36:03,940 --> 00:36:08,911
[Real Capital &amp; Global Partners
Request for Repayment]

365
00:36:14,620 --> 00:36:18,220
So 12% of one billion won is 120 million won?

366
00:36:18,220 --> 00:36:20,220
What is going on?

367
00:36:42,035 --> 00:36:44,875
Yeah, I can handle this.

368
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,740
Hi.

369
00:37:03,540 --> 00:37:04,848
This is Jeon Yang Ja.

370
00:37:04,848 --> 00:37:07,594
Put it on speakerphone.

371
00:37:09,144 --> 00:37:11,556
Is anyone there?

372
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:18,697
Yes, nice to meet you.

373
00:37:18,697 --> 00:37:20,947
Where's my daughter?

374
00:37:20,947 --> 00:37:22,360
Where's your son-in-law?

375
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:24,786
Stop messing around and let me talk to her.

376
00:37:24,786 --> 00:37:30,039
If you pay me, your daughter will come home
without a scratch.

377
00:37:30,039 --> 00:37:33,545
Do you actually have my daughter?

378
00:37:33,545 --> 00:37:37,969
Who kidnaps people like this nowadays?

379
00:37:45,599 --> 00:37:49,476
You shouldn't yell at him like that.

380
00:37:58,487 --> 00:38:02,405
Yi Gyeong! Sweetheart!

381
00:38:02,405 --> 00:38:05,340
- Yi Gyeong!
- Take that off!

382
00:38:05,340 --> 00:38:09,840
- Please don't touch her.
- Yi Gyeong!

383
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,875
Please, don't touch her.

384
00:38:11,875 --> 00:38:15,176
Yi Gyeong...

385
00:38:29,349 --> 00:38:31,687
[Unknown Number]

386
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:35,941
Hello.

387
00:38:35,941 --> 00:38:38,068
Get three billion won ready.

388
00:38:38,068 --> 00:38:42,114
Tonight at 10pm, Bukwang Sky Road parking lot.
See you there.

389
00:38:42,114 --> 00:38:44,679
Tonight? Wait a second.

390
00:38:52,566 --> 00:38:54,720
Listen to me.

391
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,336
He sounds like a professional.

392
00:38:56,336 --> 00:38:59,016
He sounds like he knows what he's doing.

393
00:39:01,086 --> 00:39:03,771
He said three billion won, right?

394
00:39:04,803 --> 00:39:07,514
Yes, ma'am.

395
00:39:07,514 --> 00:39:10,309
What if we put one billion in cash on top

396
00:39:10,309 --> 00:39:15,500
and fill the rest with newspaper?

397
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:16,565
Sorry, what?

398
00:39:16,565 --> 00:39:21,506
That's what they do in the movies.

399
00:39:21,506 --> 00:39:26,575
If I put 10,000 won bills on top

400
00:39:26,575 --> 00:39:29,655
it'll be hard for him to check.

401
00:39:31,506 --> 00:39:33,759
That won't work.

402
00:39:35,751 --> 00:39:38,191
We need to call the police.

403
00:39:40,072 --> 00:39:43,342
If we make him angry...

404
00:39:43,342 --> 00:39:45,789
it could put her life in danger...

405
00:39:49,932 --> 00:39:54,507
Her safety has to come first.

406
00:40:04,027 --> 00:40:05,123
[Divorce lawyer, Hwang Min Jeong]

407
00:40:05,123 --> 00:40:07,383
It's always the same story.

408
00:40:08,283 --> 00:40:09,785
Excuse me?

409
00:40:09,785 --> 00:40:14,106
I stopped by just in case.
I'm not going to get a divorce anytime soon.

410
00:40:14,106 --> 00:40:16,520
That's what you're thinking, isn't it?

411
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:18,540
Well...

412
00:40:19,139 --> 00:40:21,479
That's how it starts.

413
00:40:22,540 --> 00:40:24,217
You're a housekeeper?

414
00:40:24,911 --> 00:40:27,186
- Yes.
- Any children?

415
00:40:27,186 --> 00:40:28,892
She's going to college.

416
00:40:28,892 --> 00:40:31,580
So you'll need money, then.

417
00:40:31,580 --> 00:40:32,840
Excuse me?

418
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:37,180
You need to find out
how much can you get before the divorce.

419
00:40:53,486 --> 00:40:58,000
<i>Try not to let your feelings get in the way.</i>

420
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:03,572
<i>Identifying assets is the most important thing
and it helps if your husband is at fault.</i>

421
00:41:13,208 --> 00:41:14,827
Se Yoon Buliding...

422
00:41:14,827 --> 00:41:17,154
[52 Sejeong-ro, Yongdaemun District, Seoul]
Se Yoon Buliding.

423
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:25,541
[Official land price KRW 2.4 billion
Debt 1.2 billion, Bank loan 1 billion Won]

424
00:41:27,070 --> 00:41:29,987
There's nothing left but debt.

425
00:41:32,159 --> 00:41:35,359
[I am a woman in my late 40s
who stopped working...]

426
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:40,760
[If you are in that situation, your
competitiveness in the job market is low...]

427
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:46,200
[What now? I am fighting against a world
worse than my cheating husband.]

428
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:16,613
<i>You mean if the spouse is at fault?</i>

429
00:42:16,613 --> 00:42:21,253
<i>It could be something like having an affair.</i>

430
00:42:32,740 --> 00:42:36,460
Hey, you did a great job.

431
00:42:37,305 --> 00:42:39,518
Now all we have to do is meet her
and make the exchange

432
00:42:39,518 --> 00:42:44,198
I'll bring the money, so you bring Yi Gyeong.

433
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:48,277
So don't call me from now on.

434
00:42:48,277 --> 00:42:51,572
She might come along.

435
00:42:51,572 --> 00:42:55,950
Then I guess I should bring that mask.

436
00:42:57,828 --> 00:42:59,600
You're right.

437
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:01,640
- That's true.
- Yes.

438
00:43:01,640 --> 00:43:06,795
She knows you, so don't say anything
when you're there.

439
00:43:06,795 --> 00:43:08,297
Got it?

440
00:43:08,297 --> 00:43:11,341
So you park your car over there...

441
00:43:11,341 --> 00:43:14,341
- Give me 1.5 billion won.
- What?

442
00:43:16,803 --> 00:43:18,973
Give me 1.5 billion won.

443
00:43:22,459 --> 00:43:25,301
I think I've earned it.

444
00:43:28,060 --> 00:43:30,770
[Seoul Yongdaemun Police Station]

445
00:43:38,243 --> 00:43:40,060
Hey.

446
00:43:40,060 --> 00:43:42,893
I found a video of Gyun's accident.
Want to see it?

447
00:43:42,893 --> 00:43:45,253
Yeah? Where did you get it?

448
00:43:45,253 --> 00:43:48,670
A delivery bike's black box caught it.

449
00:43:48,670 --> 00:43:52,580
It's pretty far away and hard to see, but...

450
00:43:56,786 --> 00:43:58,480
Hold on.

451
00:43:58,480 --> 00:43:59,848
Look at this guy.

452
00:43:59,848 --> 00:44:01,968
Zoom in on him.

453
00:44:04,906 --> 00:44:09,233
Isn't that Gyun's brother-in-law?

454
00:44:09,233 --> 00:44:12,277
It looks like him...

455
00:44:12,277 --> 00:44:14,287
but there's no way.

456
00:44:15,219 --> 00:44:17,822
- What are you all doing?
- Sir.

457
00:44:17,822 --> 00:44:21,954
I was looking at the video of Gyun's accident
and found something.

458
00:44:21,954 --> 00:44:24,373
- This guy right here...
- Look.

459
00:44:24,373 --> 00:44:27,543
I know you're upset,
but it's just a hit-and-run.

460
00:44:27,543 --> 00:44:30,760
The driver was already wanted.

461
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:36,090
Also about Jeong Chang Su, and Real Capital
Gyun was investigating...

462
00:44:36,090 --> 00:44:39,200
I told you to drop it, remember?

463
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:41,223
But the circumstances are...

464
00:44:41,223 --> 00:44:45,057
You can't go after a foreign company
without a good reason.

465
00:44:45,057 --> 00:44:47,790
If you want to investigate
bring me some real evidence.

466
00:44:47,790 --> 00:44:52,690
- Like Jeong Chang Su's body, for god's sake.
- Sir.

467
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:56,405
Forget about that...
We got a case so get ready to move.

468
00:44:56,405 --> 00:44:58,186
Sir? What case all of a sudden?

469
00:44:58,186 --> 00:45:01,324
Good, you guys all come with me.
Bo Ram, you too!

470
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:03,662
Where are we going? Sir, can you tell us?

471
00:45:03,662 --> 00:45:05,942
Come on!

472
00:45:57,080 --> 00:45:59,940
- Mr. Min, you are here.
- Hello.

473
00:45:59,940 --> 00:46:03,511
Hey, put a wire on him.

474
00:46:03,511 --> 00:46:07,091
Hi, could you take off your jacket?
Your jacket.

475
00:46:07,091 --> 00:46:11,399
- Sure, here you go.
- I'll take that.

476
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:16,652
It's for your safety, so please bear with it.

477
00:46:16,652 --> 00:46:21,612
There is a power button here. Press it
and turn it off when you go to the bathroom.

478
00:46:21,612 --> 00:46:26,912
You must turn it on when we get there.
Would you put this in your ear?

479
00:46:26,912 --> 00:46:29,520
Try not to be too nervous.

480
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:31,583
- Hwal Seong.
- Yes.

481
00:46:31,583 --> 00:46:34,346
Just work with them.

482
00:46:34,346 --> 00:46:36,156
Okay.

483
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:44,888
- Thanks for helping us out.
- No problem.

484
00:46:49,539 --> 00:46:53,599
Why did you call the police?
I told you already...

485
00:46:54,599 --> 00:46:58,526
You want me to just hand over
three billion won? Please.

486
00:47:00,153 --> 00:47:05,621
Things could get really messy
if the police get involved.

487
00:47:07,658 --> 00:47:11,357
Let the professionals take care of this.

488
00:48:04,715 --> 00:48:06,261
Let's get going.

489
00:48:06,261 --> 00:48:09,970
You all go ahead and wait. Ju Ran, Bo Ram,

490
00:48:09,970 --> 00:48:12,267
and I will follow Mr. Min, alright?

491
00:48:12,267 --> 00:48:14,316
Yes, sir.

492
00:48:18,060 --> 00:48:20,580
Look.

493
00:48:23,340 --> 00:48:25,880
Please make sure this gets done.

494
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:32,827
God, you really need to be more careful.
Things aren't like they used to be.

495
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:35,624
I can come with you, can't I?

496
00:48:35,624 --> 00:48:37,514
You want to come too?

497
00:48:38,293 --> 00:48:42,130
I can ride with you.

498
00:48:42,130 --> 00:48:46,260
Oh, that's not really safe, though.

499
00:48:46,260 --> 00:48:51,200
This is about my money and my daughter.
I will be in the car, so don't worry.

500
00:48:52,891 --> 00:48:54,891
Yes, ma'am.

501
00:49:09,351 --> 00:49:12,784
Don't worry. We'll be with you.

502
00:49:15,419 --> 00:49:18,499
I need to use the bathroom.

503
00:49:33,839 --> 00:49:37,194
<i>The cops are onto us. Just stay on foot.</i>

504
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:50,206
[T C A O U J S F]

505
00:49:50,206 --> 00:49:52,948
We need to leave now to get there on time.

506
00:49:52,948 --> 00:49:57,371
Okay, I'm coming out now.

507
00:50:33,534 --> 00:50:35,424
God.

508
00:51:30,090 --> 00:51:32,210
Sir.

509
00:51:33,739 --> 00:51:36,739
Hey, Dong Gi.

510
00:51:43,586 --> 00:51:47,149
Why didn't you ask me to help you?

511
00:51:47,149 --> 00:51:50,403
- I didn't want to bother you.
- Come on.

512
00:51:52,905 --> 00:51:54,690
Why is it so heavy?

513
00:51:56,553 --> 00:51:59,451
There were a few things left.

514
00:52:03,499 --> 00:52:05,076
Your brother-in-law's stuff?

515
00:52:05,076 --> 00:52:10,840
Yeah, there's still a lot of stuff in there.
I need to clear it out soon.

516
00:52:10,840 --> 00:52:13,842
Okay, come on.

517
00:52:13,842 --> 00:52:17,602
You couldn't have possibly carried this alone.

518
00:52:19,139 --> 00:52:23,807
This isn't working.
You pull, and I'll push from behind.

519
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:25,053
I'm exhausted.

520
00:52:28,145 --> 00:52:31,191
Support the bottom.

521
00:52:34,939 --> 00:52:38,530
- Okay, this is good, right here.
- Here?

522
00:52:38,530 --> 00:52:41,847
Yes, thank you so much.

523
00:52:42,996 --> 00:52:45,279
I am good now. Thank you.

524
00:52:45,279 --> 00:52:47,372
I was wondering...

525
00:52:47,372 --> 00:52:49,092
since...

526
00:52:49,795 --> 00:52:54,074
I helped you move this
can you help me with something?

527
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:57,199
Help you with what?

528
00:52:58,136 --> 00:53:02,256
Moving that plant over there.

529
00:53:04,977 --> 00:53:07,646
- Sure.
- Right now.

530
00:53:07,646 --> 00:53:10,026
- Yes.
- Okay.

531
00:53:17,778 --> 00:53:20,858
My Mom saw this when she
went to Vietnam 22 years ago.

532
00:53:20,858 --> 00:53:22,536
Back then, it was just a small seedling.

533
00:53:22,536 --> 00:53:24,966
No, let's put this over there.

534
00:53:27,440 --> 00:53:29,334
Anyway, she bought this seedling.

535
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:32,593
Oh my, good.

536
00:53:32,593 --> 00:53:35,260
So after caring for it for 20 years...

537
00:53:35,260 --> 00:53:39,000
She gave it to me when I opened this cafe.

538
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:42,594
She told me to let it grow naturally,
just like this.

539
00:53:42,594 --> 00:53:45,494
What do you think?
Isn't it great with this cafe?

540
00:53:45,494 --> 00:53:47,269
Yes, it looks fantastic.

541
00:53:47,269 --> 00:53:50,814
- I should get going.
- You know what?

542
00:53:50,814 --> 00:53:52,066
What?

543
00:53:52,066 --> 00:53:54,735
The toilet is clogged again.

544
00:53:54,735 --> 00:53:56,419
Then I should fix it for you.

545
00:53:56,419 --> 00:53:58,589
When are you going to fix it?

546
00:54:00,833 --> 00:54:05,061
I'll fix it this weekend, okay? Take care.

547
00:54:06,034 --> 00:54:07,994
You need help?

548
00:54:07,994 --> 00:54:09,553
No, I'm good.

549
00:54:15,005 --> 00:54:18,221
He bought a car without telling me?

550
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:27,922
Please follow that car.

551
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:41,322
Go ahead, we'll follow behind you.

552
00:55:58,692 --> 00:56:00,611
Where is he going?

553
00:56:00,611 --> 00:56:02,693
Mr. Min, where are you going?

554
00:56:02,693 --> 00:56:06,673
Sorry, my stomach is upset.

555
00:56:06,673 --> 00:56:10,867
Sir, Mr. Min needs to use the bathroom.
Please go on ahead.

556
00:56:10,867 --> 00:56:13,046
Got it, make it quick.

557
00:56:36,980 --> 00:56:42,071
I'll take it out for a Moment.
Sorry about this.

558
00:58:01,593 --> 00:58:03,524
Hey, what are you doing?

559
00:58:06,528 --> 00:58:08,800
Is there a pay phone here?

560
00:58:09,446 --> 00:58:11,686
What is a pay phone?

561
00:58:12,346 --> 00:58:15,810
It's something you put coins in to make a call.

562
00:58:16,496 --> 00:58:18,936
Why don't you use your cell phone?

563
00:58:20,140 --> 00:58:23,272
- Let me borrow your phone.
- Excuse me?

564
00:58:32,429 --> 00:58:34,166
Shit.

565
00:58:44,733 --> 00:58:47,553
Damn it, it almost got me.

566
00:59:10,200 --> 00:59:12,480
Please stop here.

567
00:59:31,777 --> 00:59:33,565
Is that it?

568
00:59:38,689 --> 00:59:42,791
Hey, when are Detective Ko and Mr. Min coming?

569
00:59:42,791 --> 00:59:45,669
- Suspect is here.
- They will be here soon.

570
00:59:45,669 --> 00:59:48,469
Tell them to hurry up.

571
00:59:56,133 --> 00:59:57,828
That's it.

572
00:59:58,739 --> 01:00:00,854
- That's the one.
- Pardon?

573
01:00:11,278 --> 01:00:13,678
I should put this on.

574
01:00:28,327 --> 01:00:31,045
Damn it, I can't see anything.

575
01:00:33,160 --> 01:00:37,429
Why aren't you answering your phone, Su Jong?

576
01:00:37,429 --> 01:00:40,189
Looks like he's not answering.

577
01:00:42,100 --> 01:00:45,479
Can I have my phone back?
I need to send a text.

578
01:00:45,479 --> 01:00:47,649
- What?
- Open the text panel.

579
01:00:48,649 --> 01:00:53,180
- What text?
- Here, I don't have much time. Come on.

580
01:00:53,180 --> 01:00:54,988
Hurry up.

581
01:00:54,988 --> 01:00:56,738
Here.

582
01:01:01,386 --> 01:01:04,748
What is this? What kind of key pad is this?

583
01:01:04,748 --> 01:01:07,042
You enter the text.

584
01:01:07,042 --> 01:01:08,852
Come on.

585
01:01:08,852 --> 01:01:10,016
What do you want to say?

586
01:01:10,016 --> 01:01:13,090
- The cops are onto you. Run.
- Excuse me?

587
01:01:13,090 --> 01:01:15,843
No, it's nothing like that. Come on.

588
01:01:15,843 --> 01:01:18,948
I think I might be running late.

589
01:01:22,230 --> 01:01:23,840
Yes.

590
01:01:24,852 --> 01:01:26,612
Well...

591
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:31,430
I'm trying to catch a kidnapper.

592
01:01:39,373 --> 01:01:43,213
Yes, sure.

593
01:02:03,050 --> 01:02:05,220
5,400 won, please.

594
01:02:05,906 --> 01:02:08,046
Can I have a receipt?

595
01:02:19,072 --> 01:02:21,400
Thank you.

596
01:02:21,400 --> 01:02:24,660
- Have a good night.
- You too.

597
01:02:41,630 --> 01:02:44,680
I can't see anything.

598
01:02:50,263 --> 01:02:52,723
God damn it.

599
01:03:22,928 --> 01:03:26,026
Why is he running so late?

600
01:03:26,026 --> 01:03:29,130
Drive slowly towards the parking lot.

601
01:03:29,130 --> 01:03:32,580
We'll be right behind you, so don't worry.

602
01:04:02,509 --> 01:04:06,549
Sir, it's Bo Ram. We're here now.

603
01:04:08,557 --> 01:04:12,644
- Will everything be alright?
- Don't worry.

604
01:04:12,644 --> 01:04:17,534
Detective Ko, tell Mr. Min to just act normal.

605
01:04:18,540 --> 01:04:21,595
Just try to relax and be yourself.

606
01:04:32,039 --> 01:04:33,909
Come on.

607
01:04:39,466 --> 01:04:41,556
What is he saying?

608
01:04:54,645 --> 01:04:57,189
We have a suspect in sight.

609
01:04:57,189 --> 01:05:01,508
- What? What the hell are you saying?
- Cops!

610
01:05:03,358 --> 01:05:07,186
Stop messing around.
You got your money, right?

611
01:05:09,595 --> 01:05:14,289
Put the money in the car
and give me back my wife.

612
01:05:14,289 --> 01:05:17,140
- Why are you talking to me like...
- Stop it!

613
01:05:17,140 --> 01:05:19,770
Stop talking! I don't want to hear it.

614
01:05:19,770 --> 01:05:22,390
Where is my wife?

615
01:05:23,033 --> 01:05:26,513
- Are you acting too?
- Where is my wife?

616
01:05:26,513 --> 01:05:29,471
- Is your mother-in-law here?
- Come on! My wife!

617
01:05:29,471 --> 01:05:31,833
My wife! Where is she?

618
01:05:31,833 --> 01:05:33,725
- You crazy bastard.
- Where is she?

619
01:05:33,725 --> 01:05:35,561
She's in the trunk.

620
01:05:35,561 --> 01:05:37,855
Yi Gyeong, honey, come on.

621
01:05:37,855 --> 01:05:40,055
Get ready to move in.

622
01:05:46,620 --> 01:05:49,740
Secure all locations and stay ready.

623
01:05:49,740 --> 01:05:51,540
Hey.

624
01:05:54,610 --> 01:05:57,720
Hey, you can't get out of the car yet.

625
01:05:57,720 --> 01:06:02,910
You have to catch him now.
What if he just runs off with my money?

626
01:06:06,460 --> 01:06:08,177
What the hell is this?

627
01:06:08,177 --> 01:06:09,340
You!

628
01:06:09,340 --> 01:06:11,860
Come on!

629
01:06:20,689 --> 01:06:23,113
I am so sorry!

630
01:06:32,659 --> 01:06:34,589
Catch him!

631
01:06:40,890 --> 01:06:42,740
Get him!

632
01:06:45,790 --> 01:06:48,970
Open the door! Come on!

633
01:06:48,970 --> 01:06:53,140
You are surrounded! Open the door!

634
01:07:20,541 --> 01:07:22,042
<i>Have you seen his face?</i>

635
01:07:22,042 --> 01:07:24,510
<i>What happened to your hand?
It looks suspicious.</i>

636
01:07:24,510 --> 01:07:27,626
<i>Do you understand what happened?
Your daughter was kidnapped...</i>

637
01:07:27,626 --> 01:07:30,592
<i>- What is this?
- It's my backpack.</i>

638
01:07:30,592 --> 01:07:32,910
<i>So what's in it?</i>

639
01:07:32,910 --> 01:07:37,474
<i>Three billion won.
He took three billion won as ransom for you.</i>

640
01:07:37,474 --> 01:07:38,510
<i>This is nice.</i>

641
01:07:38,510 --> 01:07:40,556
<i>So, is this the criminal you saw last night?</i>

642
01:07:40,556 --> 01:07:42,938
<i>You are under arrest
for robbery and kidnapping.</i>

643
01:07:42,938 --> 01:07:47,358
<i>Let go! Get off of me!</i>
